The paper deals with the problem of sparse robust linear regression, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and social and information networks (cs.SI). The use of compressed sensing techniques to deal with sparse noise is also a common theme in cs.IT and cs.LG. Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely candidates for this paper.
